<br>
Talk to Mavuin in the basement cellblock. Hail him and follow the dialogue. He will ask you to plead his case before the Tribunal, aggreeing will grant you a character flag. <br>
<br>
Head to the area with The Tribunal, and ask them about Mavuin. Following the dialog, saying &quot;I am prepared&quot; to each Tribunal will give you description of the six trials. <br>
<br>
To do this one, say &quot;I am ready to begin the trial of flame.&quot; Make sure you are actually prepared when you say that because your group will be teleported to the event area where you will only get a few seconds before things start. <br>
<br>
This one puts you in one of the open rooms with a pillar in the middle. 4 mobs will spawn, either imps or fIre elementals. Blementals are mezzable, imps are not. During the fights, 3 different AB's will be cast throughout the room. Searing Heat (100 fr debufflasting 6.5 min), Fiery Death (400 hp dd, 1 dispell), and Wave of Heat (200 hp per tick dot) are the 3 spells. Resists seemed decent with -350 fr, however many members of the group got important buffs such as Virtue dispelled! I assume 4 rounds then boss again like always. On a side note, you lose this trial if a mob remains in <br>
the middle of the room (near the pillar) for around 1.5 minutes or so, so the tactic is to pull them all to the side of the room and mez them/fight them there. <br>
<br>
Finishing this gives you the Mark of Flame. <br>
<br>
Now talk to the Tribunal and say &quot;what evidence of Mauvuin&quot; and they will tell you that they have consented to hear Mauvuin's case. Head back down and talk to him and he will ask you to go see Karana and Mithaniel Marr. This will flag you to be able to enter the Plane of Storms and and Plane Valor. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
